0%A0%D1%83%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%B0%D0%BD-%D0%9C%D1%8A%D0%B9%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2/%D0%91%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%BA%D0%B0/|title=\u0411\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430\u043b\u043a\u0430 by \u0420\u0443\u0441\u043b\u0430\u043d \u041c\u044a\u0439\u043d\u043e\u0432 on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''\u0414\u0430\u0439 \u043c\u0438 \u0446\u0435\u043b\u0443\u0432\u043a\u0430'' <small>/ Give me a kiss /</small> (in [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] by Tonita)\n* ''\u0425\u0438\u0449\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430'' <small>/ Predator /</small> (in [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] by Extra Nina)\n* ''Pusz-pussz'' (in [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] by [[Pa-D\u00f6-D\u0151]], 2003<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Pa-D%C3%B6-D%C5%91-Had-%C3%89nekelj%C3%BCnk-Mi-Is-Az-Id%C3%A9n/release/7431520|title=Pa-D\u00f6-D\u0151 - Had' \u00c9nekelj\u00fcnk Mi Is Az Id\u00e9n!|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Kiss-Kiss'' <small>/ TCM-istele /</small> (in [[Romanian Language|Romanian]] by Vacan\u021ba Mare in Cu oltenii la eclips\u0103 show.)\n* ''Poljubi me'' <small>/ Kiss Me /</small> (in [[Slovenian language|Slovenian]] by Sandi Selim\u010di\u010d)\n* ''T\u00eb M\u00eb Jap\u00ebsh Nj\u00eb Puthje'' (in [[Albanian language|Albanian]] by Shk\u00eblqim Kola)\n\n==Samplings and adaptations==\n===Dj R'AN version===\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Kiss Kiss\n| cover      = Kiss-Kiss-DJ-RAN-Mohombi-Big-Ali.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = DJ R'AN featuring [[Mohombi]] and [[Big Ali]]\n| album      =\n| released   = September 26, 2016\n| format     = [[CD single]], downloads\n| recorded   = 2016\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]\n| length     = 2:51\n| label      = Madison Music\n| composer   =\n| lyricist   =\n| producer   = DJ R'AN\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|WMCDx2edfU8|\"Kiss Kiss\" by DJ R'AN feat. Mohombi and Big Ali}} }}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|fzvVl9ULUXk|\"Kiss Kiss\" by Ardian Bujupi and DJ R'AN feat. Mohombi and Big Ali}} }}\n}}\n* In 2016, French Dj R'AN (also known as Lucenzo Dj) released an adapted version of the song with new lyrics and added music. The single also titled \"Kiss Kiss\" and featured vocals by Swedish [[Mohombi]] and American [[Big Ali]] with additional work by [[Willy William]]. A music video was also released.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WMCDx2edfU8 YouTube Dj R'AN channel - Dj R'AN - KISS KISS feat Mohombi & Big Ali (official clip)]</ref> \n\nAn alternative release of the DJ R'AN version of \"Kiss Kiss\" was done in 2017 by Kosovar-German singer [[Ardian Bujupi]] with Dj R'AN featuring Mohombi and Big Ali.\n\n'''Other samplings'''\n* [[Yosi Piamenta]] released a version quoting ''Kol Hamesameach'', a [[Hebrew language]] passage from the [[Talmud]], but set to the melody of the song \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whosampled.com/Piamenta/Kol-Hamesameach/|title=Kol Hamesameach by Piamenta on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>\n* An Israeli 6PM news program on [[Channel 10 (Israel)|Channel 10]] named [[London et Kirschenbaum]] (named after the hosts, [[Yaron London]] and the program's late host [[Moti Kirschenbaum]]) is using a sample of this song in its opening theme.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://tarkantr.blogspot.com Single and Song Lyrics Information] in English\n* [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0209933/ ''Beau Travail'' at IMDB]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0245573/soundtrack ''XX/XY'' at IMDB]\n* {{MetroLyrics song|stella-soleil|kiss-kiss|Full English lyrics}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{tarkan}}\n{{Holly Valance}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Simarik}}\n[[Category:1999 singles]]\n[[Category:Tarkan (singer) songs]]\n[[Category:Ultratop 50 Singles (Wallonia) number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Tarkan (singer)]]\n[[Category:Turkish-language songs]]\n[[Category:2001 singles]]\n[[Category:2002 debut singles]]\n[[Category:Holly Valance songs]]\n[[Category:English-language Turkish songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Scotland]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Hype Williams]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Tim Royes]]\n[[Category:1997 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1997 single by Tarkan}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\n| cover      = Simarik.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]]\n| album      = [[Tarkan (album)|Tarkan]] & [[\u00d6l\u00fcr\u00fcm Sana (album)|\u00d6l\u00fcr\u00fcm Sana]]\n| released   = 1997\n| format     = [[CD single]], [[Gramophone record|LP]]\n| recorded   = 1997\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Turkish pop music|Turkish pop]], [[dance-pop]]\n| length     = {{plainlist|\n* 3:10 (\"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" radio edit only)\n* 3:57 (original version)\n}}\n| label      = ''Urban''/''Polygram''/''[[Universal Music|Universal]]''\n| writer     = [[Sezen Aksu]], [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]]\n| producer   = Mehmet S\u00f6\u011f\u00fcto\u011flu, [[Dieter Rubach]]\n| prev_title = [[Sal\u0131na Sal\u0131na Sinsice]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title = [[\u015e\u0131k\u0131d\u0131m]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = Alternative cover\n | type    = studio\n | cover   = Music album record Simarikalternate.jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = CD2 single cover\n}}\n}}\n\"'''\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k'''\" ({{IPA-tr|\u0283\u026fma\u02c8\u027e\u026fk|pron}}, \"Spoilt\"), also known as \"'''Kiss Kiss'''\", is a [[1997 in music|1997]] song by Turkish singer [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]]. It was written by [[Sezen Aksu]], with music credited as composed by Tarkan. However, Tarkan later admitted in a 2006 interview that this had been done without Aksu's consent, who was the true copyright owner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tarkandeluxe.blogspot.com/2006/03/tarkan-confesses.html |title=Tarkan Deluxe: Tarkan Confesses |publisher=Tarkandeluxe.blogspot.com |date=2006-03-30 |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref> It formed part of Tarkan's album ''[[\u00d6l\u00fcr\u00fcm Sana (album)|\u00d6l\u00fcr\u00fcm Sana]]''. \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" was released in [[France]] in 1998 and the rest of the world in 1999, from the [[compilation album]] ''Tarkan'', which was released in [[Europe]]. It has sold two million copies all across Europe. Many versions of the song were recorded in different languages, most notably the English-language cover, titled \"Kiss Kiss\", by [[Greece|Greek]]-[[United States|American]] singer [[Stella Soleil]] in 2001 which was itself covered by [[Australia]]n actress [[Holly Valance]] in 2002.\n\n==The song==\nAs Tarkan's first major single, the song is generally considered his debut single. He had released three albums before this, but never released a song in single format due to the album-orientated nature of the Turkish music industry. The song has also appeared in soundtracks of various movies, including French film ''[[Beau travail]]'' and the American film ''[[XX/XY]]''. It is generally considered Tarkan's signature song in Europe. Its chorus ends with two characteristic [[kiss]] sounds.\n\n==Music video==\nThe [[music video]] is shot in Marseille, France with narrow streets and cobbled roads, with Tarkan [[singing]] and [[jaywalking]]. Several females on the streets see him and start following him to try to [[kiss]] him, but he tries to avoid them by first changing direction and then later by walking faster. More and more women begin to follow him as the song proceeds, but Tarkan eventually starts running in order to avoid them. A big group of women then run after him and as the song finishes, Tarkan takes cover in a street corner. A young girl is there as well and Tarkan kisses her [[forehead]].\n\n==Track listings==\n{{multiple image\n| footer    = Single versions\n| width     = 120\n| image1    = S1 simariklp promo.JPG\n| alt1      =\n| image2    = Lpsimarik 1.JPG\n| alt2      =\n| image3    = Lp simarik3.jpg\n| alt3      =\n}}\n* ''\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k'', 1999\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Malagutti (4:46)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Malagutti edit remix (3:17)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Malagutti extended remix (7:00)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Ned Divine edit remix (3:13)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Ned Divine extended remix (5:56)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k radio edit(3:12)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k long (original) version (3:55)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Or\u0131ental (4:05)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Z\u0131o dub extended remix (6:11)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k Z\u0131o dub edit remix\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k \u015e\u0131nan soulful (6:14)\n# \u015e\u0131mar\u0131k \u015e\u0131nan dub\nTrack lists to this CD single change depending on the country of release, e.g. [[United States|America]] and Germany.\n\nThere were four promotional [[Vinyl LP|LP]] versions released.\nA promotional CD single was released in France, with an orange cover. This was the first ever release and included one track. This is now a collector's item. There was also a limited edition (fan-edition) single released in Germany, which came with a poster of Tarkan.\n\n==Commercial performance==\nWhen the single was released in Europe, it reached No. 1 in Belgium, No. 2 in Norway, plus No. 3 in Switzerland,<ref>{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://swisscharts.com/showitem.asp?key=3894&cat=s |title=Tarkan - Simarik |publisher=swisscharts.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref> France, Germany and the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.top40web.nl/salestop40/jaarlijsten/jr1999.html |title=Sales Top 40 |publisher=Top40web.nl |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref> Sales went [[Gold album|gold]] in Europe, where Tarkan was presented with his gold disc at [[Cannes|Cannes Midem]] and in Germany by Universal<ref>{{cite web|title=Award for Pop Singer Tarkan|url=http://www.byegm.gov.tr/YAYINLARIMIZ/chr/ING99/10/99x10x11.HTM#%2018|publisher=Turkish Press Review|accessdate=25 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/19991127213631/http://www.byegm.gov.tr/YAYINLARIMIZ/chr/ING99/10/99x10x11.HTM#%2018|archivedate=27 November 1999|date=10 November 1999}}</ref> and [[Platinum single|platinum]] in [[Latin America]] where it knocked [[Enrique Iglesias]] off the top slot.\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1998\u201399)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|14|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|5|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|1|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n|Denmark ([[IFPI Denmark|IFPI]])<ref>Danish Singles Chart 17 September 1999</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|16\n|-\n|Europe ([[Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1998/MM-1998-11-28.pdf|title=Music & Media: Eurochart Hot 100|accessdate=20 June 2018|work=[[Music & Media]]}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|10 \n|-\n{{singlechart|France|3|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany|6|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|3|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|3|artist=Tarkan|song=Simarik|accessdate=27 June 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|2|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Portugal|19|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|3|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|3|artist=Tarkan|song=\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n!Chart (1998)\n!Position\n|-\n|Belgium (Ultratop Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1998&cat=s|title=Jaaroverzichten 1998|publisher=Ultratop|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|33\n|-\n|Belgium (Ultratop Wallonia)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/annual.asp?year=1998&cat=s|title=Rapports Annuels 1998|publisher=Ultratop|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|5 \n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n!Chart (1999)\n!Position\n|-\n|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-1999 |title=Top 100 Single-Jahrescharts|language=German |publisher=[[GfK Entertainment]] |accessdate=21 April 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|26\n|-\n|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/1999|title=Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 1999|publisher=Dutch Top 40|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|14\n|-\n|Netherlands (Single Top 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1999&cat=s|title=Jaaroverzichten \u2013 Single 1999|website=dutchcharts.nl|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|18\n|-\n|Sweden (Sverigetopplistan)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/43?dspy=1999&dspp=1|title=\u00c5rslista Singlar \u2013 \u00c5r 1999|publisher=Sverigetopplistan|language=Swedish|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|24\n|-\n|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/charts/jahreshitparade/1999|title=Schweizer Jahreshitparade 1999 \u2013 hitparade.ch|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|17\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Usage in media==\n\"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" was featured in films and soap opera including ''[[Beau travail]]'', ''[[Roman\u00e9]]''  and ''[[XX/XY]]''.\n\n\"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" was using with sound effect of Tarkan kiss sounds including in several Chilean television program including: ''[[Calle 7]]'', ''Yingo'', ''En portada'', ''[[Buenos D\u00edas a Todos]]'', ''[[Muy buenos d\u00edas]]'', ''[[Mucho gusto (Chilean TV program)|Mucho gusto]]'', ''Gente como t\u00fa'', ''[[La ma\u00f1ana de Chilevisi\u00f3n]]'' and others.\n\n==Stella Soleil version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Kiss Kiss\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Stella Soleil]]\n| album      = Dirty Little Secret\n| released   = April 24, 2001\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 2000\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]\n| length     = 3:01 <small>(radio edit)</small>\n| label      = [[Universal Records|Universal]]\n| writer     = Juliette Jaimes, [[Sezen Aksu]], [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]], Steve Welton-Jaimes\n| producer   = Darren Bennett, Steve Welton-Jaimes\n| prev_title = Torch\n| prev_year  = 2001\n| next_title = Pretty Young Thing\n| next_year  = 2002\n}}\n\"'''Kiss Kiss'''\" is the debut single by American recording artist [[Stella Soleil]]. The single is a cremake of the [[Music of Turkey|Turkish]] song \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" by [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]] with new lyrics. The English version was credited to by Juliette Jaimes, Sezen Aksu, [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]], and Steve Welton-Jaimes. The single was released to mainstream radio in April 2001. The single was also released in regions of Europe, excluding the UK.\n\n===Music video===\nThe music video is set on the beach during the late night. The video (directed by [[Hype Williams]]) shows Soleil dancing on the sand, while scenes go back and forth from birds eye views of landscape around the beach.\n\n===Track listing===\n* US promotional single<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Stella-Soleil-Kiss-Kiss/release/925156 |title=Stella Soleil - Kiss Kiss (CD) at Discogs |publisher=Discogs.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref>\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" <small>(Radio Version)</small>\n* US 12\" promotional single<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Stella-Soleil-Kiss-Kiss/release/1503235 |title=Stella Soleil - Kiss Kiss (Vinyl) at Discogs |publisher=Discogs.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref>\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" <small>(main version)</small>\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" <small>(instrumental)</small>\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" <small>(main version)</small><!-- not a mistake, it's the same version again -->\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" <small>(a cappella)</small>\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Chart (2001)\n! scope=\"col\" | Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardpopsongs|27|artist=Holly Valance}}\n|}\n\n==Holly Valance version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Kiss Kiss\n| cover      = Kiss kiss - limited edition.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Holly Valance]]\n| album      = [[Footprints (album)|Footprints]]\n| released   = 29 April 2002\n| format     = [[CD single]], [[Cassette single]]\n| recorded   = 2002\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]\n| length     = 3:23\n| label      = [[London Records|London]]\n| writer     = Juliette Jaimes, Sezen Aksu, [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]], Steve Welton-Jaimes\n| producer   = Darren Bennett, Steve Welton-Jaimes\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Down Boy]]\n| next_year  = 2002\n}}\n\n\"Kiss Kiss\" is the debut recording by Australian actress [[Holly Valance]]. Her version is a remake of the 2001 song of the same name by Stella Soleil, itself a remake of \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" by [[Tarkan (singer)|Tarkan]]. The single was released in April 2002 in Australia and United Kingdom,<ref name=\"UK\"/> and shot straight to number one in both countries.\n\n===Music video===\nThe official music video for Holly Valance\u2019s version features a compilation of Valance herself with a variety of different looks and sexualised outfits whilst performing the song, all of them showed Valance wearing a violet skimpy outfit sitting on a round like chair with two disc-jockeys beside her. the second showed her dancing around red and blue neon lights, the third showed her wearing a black sparkling dress with wet hair and six male dancers dancing with her and the fourth showed Valance dancing around naked in a room full of flashing lightbulbs. There were even close-ups of Valance\u2019s lips with red sparkly lip-gloss on blowing kisses to the screen.\n\n===Commercial performance===\nThe single also debuted at number-one in the United Kingdom on 5 May 2002, selling 143,408 copies in its first week.<ref name=\"UK\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/zoom.php?id=925 |title=Holly Valance &#124; Artist |publisher=Official Charts |accessdate=2014-04-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091230124404/http://theofficialcharts.com/zoom.php?id=925 |archivedate=2009-12-30 }}</ref> The song made its debut on the Australian [[ARIA Charts]], [[UK Singles Chart]] and  [[Turkish Singles Chart]] at number one, it was Valance's first number one single. It went on to spend nine weeks in the ARIA Charts top ten, thirteen weeks in the top twenty and a total of seventeen weeks in the top fifty. In countries like [[Ireland]],  [[Finland]], [[Italy]] and [[Taiwan]] the song went to peak in the top ten. It also reached the Top 20 in [[Austria]], [[Greece]], [[Sweden]], [[Germany]], [[Japan]], [[New Zealand]], [[Switzerland]] and [[Denmark]]. It was certified Platinum by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]] and Gold by the [[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]].\n\n===ARIA awards===\n\"Kiss Kiss\" was nominated for four [[ARIA Music Awards|ARIA Awards]] at the 16th ARIA Awards in 2002.\n\n===Track listing===\n;Australian CD single\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Wise Buddha mix) \u2014 3:25\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Jah Wobble remix) \u2014 5:15\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Agent Sumo 2) \u2014 7:41\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Stargate R&B mix) \u2014 3:02\n\n;UK CD single\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Wise Buddha mix) \u2014 3:25\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Jah Wobble remix) \u2014 5:15\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Agent Sumo 2) \u2014 7:41\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Stargate R&B mix) \u2014 3:02\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (music video)\n\n;Germany CD single/UK Cassette Single\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Wise Buddha mix) \u2014 3:25\n# \"Kiss Kiss\" (Stargate R&B mix) \u2014 3:02\n\n===Charts===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Weekly charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2002)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|1|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|11|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss|accessdate=2010-12-08}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|28|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia Tip|12|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Denmark|20|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n|Europe ([[European Hot 100 Singles|Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/00s/2002/MM-2002-05-18.pdf|title=Eurochart Hot 100 Singles|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=20|issue=21|page=8|date=18 May 2002|access-date=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n{{singlechart|Finland|7|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|50|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|14|songid=5215|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Hungary|3|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss|year=2002|week=45}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|2|artist=Holly Valance}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Italy|3|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|24|year=2002|week=25}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|23|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|17|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|1|date=20020511}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|12|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|19|artist=Holly Valance|song=Kiss Kiss}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKsinglesbyname|1|artist=Holly Valance|refname=\"UK\"}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Year-end charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2002)\n!Position\n|-\n|Australia (ARIA)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/pages/aria-charts-end-of-year-charts-top-100-singles-2002.htm|title=ARIA Charts \u2013 End Of Year Charts \u2013 Top 100 Singles 2002|publisher=ARIA|accessdate=5 July 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|10\n|-\n|Austria (\u00d63 Austria Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://austriancharts.at/year.asp?cat=s&id=2002|title=Jahreshitparade Singles 2002|website=austriancharts.at|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|72\n|-\n|Europe (Eurochart Hot 100)<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/00s/2003/MM-2003-01-11.pdf|title=Year in Review \u2013 Eurochart Hot 100 Singles 2002|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=21|issue=2\u20133|page=14|date=11 January 2003|access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|69\n|-\n|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-2002|title=Top 100 Single\u2013Jahrescharts|language=German|work=GfK Entertainment|publisher=offiziellecharts.de|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|89\n|-\n|Sweden (Sverigetopplistan)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/43?dspy=2002&dspp=1|title=\u00c5rslista Singlar \u2013 \u00c5r 2002|publisher=Sverigetopplistan|language=Swedish|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|93\n|-\n|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/charts/jahreshitparade/2002|title=Schweizer Jahreshitparade 2002 \u2013 hitparade.ch|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|85\n|-\n|UK Singles (Official Charts Company)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukchartsplus.co.uk/ChartsPlusYE2002.pdf|title=The Official UK Singles Chart 2002|work=[[UKChartsPlus]]|accessdate=5 July 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|14\n|}\n\n====Certifications====\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Australia|title=Kiss Kiss|artist=Holly Valance|type=single|award=Platinum|relyear=2002|certyear=2002|accessdate=5 July 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|title=Kiss Kiss|artist=Holly Valance|type=single|award=Gold|relyear=2002|certyear=2013|accessdate=5 July 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Other cover versions==\n{{Cleanup lang|section|date=March 2020}}\nAside from \"Kiss Kiss\", there were many other covers of \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" in English and various languages, like a version sung by [[Hong Kong]] group [[EO2|E02]] in [[Cantonese]] and an [[Egypt]]ian cover version sung by [[Samy Mansour]]. Notable covers include:\n* In 1998 [[Russia]]n singer [[Filipp Kirkorov]] re-released \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" in [[Russian language|Russian]] as ''\u041f\u043e\u0446\u0435\u043b\u0443\u0439'' (''Kiss'') from the album ''\u041e\u0439, \u041c\u0430\u043c\u0430, \u0428\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0414\u0430\u043c''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/%D0%A4%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%BF%D0%BF-%D0%9A%D0%B8%D1%80%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2-%D0%9E%D0%B9-%D0%9C%D0%B0%D0%BC%D0%B0-%D0%A8%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B0-%D0%94%D0%B0%D0%BC/master/860184|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u043f \u041a\u0438\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432 - \u041e\u0439, \u041c\u0430\u043c\u0430, \u0428\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0414\u0430\u043c!|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>.\n* In 1999, [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] singer [[Viktor Pavlik]] ([[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] \u0412\u0456\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u041f\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0456\u043a) re-released \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\" in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] as \"Rozbeshchenyy\" ([[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] \u0420\u043e\u0437\u0431\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439) from the album \"Aphiny, Kyiv, Istanbul\", ukr. \u0410\u0444\u0456\u043d\u0438-\u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432-\u0406\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0431\u0443\u043b\".\n* In 2001, [[Spain|Spanish]]-[[Morocco|Moroccan]] singer [[Hakim (Spanish-Moroccan singer)|Hakim]] released ''La Muchacha Turca'' in [[Spanish language|Spanish]] as part of his album ''Entre dos orillas'', but created his own lyrics, in [[Spain]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Hakim-Entre-Dos-Orillas/release/10288824|title=Hakim (9) - Entre Dos Orillas|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>.\n* In 2006, [[South Korea]]n singer [[Shim Mina|Mina]] covered \"Kiss Kiss\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Kiss Kiss by Mina|date=2005-09-14|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/kiss-kiss/308683898?i=308683962|language=en-US|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>.\n* ''8 feles\u00e9ggel sok a baj'' <small>/ There are so many problems with 8 wives /</small> (in [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] by [[Irigy H\u00f3naljmirigy]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.xfree.hu/?n=magdyka |title=Vide\u00f3k |publisher=video.xFree.hu |date=2014-03-29 |accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref>)\n* ''La Muchacha Turca'' <small>/ Turkish Girl /</small> (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]], by Paco Ortega/[[Hakim (Spanish singer)|Hakim]], 2001<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Hakim-La-Muchacha-Turca-Simarik/master/1272943|title=Hakim (9) - La Muchacha Turca (Simarik) (Remixes)|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''La Muchacha Guapa'' <small>/ Pretty Girl /</small> (in Spanish by [[La Banda Pachuco]], 2002<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whosampled.com/Banda-Pachuco/La-Muchacha-Guapa/|title=La Muchacha Guapa by Banda Pachuco on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Ein Kuss'' <small>/ A Kiss /</small> (in [[German Language|German]] by [[Die Schl\u00fcmpfe]], 1999<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Die-Schl%C3%BCmpfe-Super-Sommer-Vol-9/release/6187593|title=Die Schl\u00fcmpfe* - Super Sommer! - Vol 9|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''\u017dene Vole Dijamante'' <small>/ Women Love Diamonds /</small> (in [[Serbian language|Serbian]] by [[Jelena Karleu\u0161a]], 1998<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/master/view/332620|title=Jelena Karleu\u0161a - Jelena Karleu\u0161a|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Ekstaza'' <small>/ Ecstasy /</small> (in [[Serbian language|Serbian]] by [[Dado Polumenta]], 2005<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/master/view/912482|title=Dado Polumenta - 100 Stepeni|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''El Bawsi'' (in [[Arabic language|Arabic]] by [[Rida and Nina Boutros]], 1999<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whosampled.com/Nina-Boutros/El-Bawsi-(%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%A9)/|title=El Bawsi (\u0627\u0644\u0628\u0648\u0633\u0629) by Nina Boutros and Reeda Boutros on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Booseh Faransavi'' (in [[Persian language|Persian]] by [[Mehran (singer)|Mehran]])\n* ''Yeki Na Doutaa'' (in [[Persian language|Persian]] by [[Sharareh]], 2000<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%87-Sharareh-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%88-Portrait/release/12325999|title=\u0634\u0631\u0627\u0631\u0647 = Sharareh* - \u062a\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0648 = Portrait|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Filakia'' (in [[Greek language|Greek]] by [[Lefteris Pantazis]], 2000<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/%CE%9B%CE%B5%CF%85%CF%84%CE%AD%CF%81%CE%B7%CF%82-%CE%A0%CE%B1%CE%BD%CF%84%CE%B1%CE%B6%CE%AE%CF%82-%CE%A6%CE%B9%CE%BB%CE%AC%CE%BA%CE%B9%CE%B1/master/830068|title=\u039b\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03ad\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b6\u03ae\u03c2 - \u03a6\u03b9\u03bb\u03ac\u03ba\u03b9\u03b1|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Neshika'' <small>/ Kiss /</small> (in [[Hebrew Language|Hebrew]] by [[Rinat Bar]], 1998<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whosampled.com/Rinat-Bar/Neshika/|title=Neshika by Rinat Bar on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''CHU!CHU!\u306f\u604b\u306e\u5408\u8a00\u8449'' (in [[Japanese Language|Japanese]] by [[Kentar\u014d Hayami]], 2000<ref>{{Citation|title=Chu!Chu!\u306f\u604b\u306e\u5408\u8a00\u8449|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/Chu-%E3%81%AF%E6%81%8B%E3%81%AE%E5%90%88%E8%A8%80%E8%91%89-%E9%80%9F%E6%B0%B4%E3%81%91%E3%82%93%E3%81%9F%E3%82%8D%E3%81%86/dp/B00005HKIE|publisher=\u30c6\u30a4\u30c1\u30af\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30c6\u30a4\u30f3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Bos'' (in [[Dari (Eastern Persian)|Dari]] by Showwkat)\n* Kiss Kiss (in English by Bodyjar, 2002<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://secondhandsongs.com/performance/6321/versions|title=Cover versions of Kiss Kiss by Bodyjar {{!}}  SecondHandSongs|website=secondhandsongs.com|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Kiss Kiss'' (in [[Cantonese language|Cantonese]] by [[EO2]] and Tiffany Lee, 2002<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yesasia.com/us/%E6%88%91%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93/1002340744-0-0-0-zh_TW/info.html|title=YESASIA : \u6211\u77e5\u9053  \u9433\u5c04\u5531\u7247 - EO2, \u767e\u4ee3\u5531\u7247 - \u7cb5\u8a9e\u97f3\u6a02 - \u90f5\u8cbb\u5168\u514d - \u5317\u7f8e\u7db2\u7ad9|website=www.yesasia.com|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Kiss (Kita Sayang Sayang)'' (in [[Indonesian language|Indonesian]] by [[Lilis Karlina]], 2001<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whosampled.com/Lilis-Karlina/Kiss-(Kita-Sayang-Sayang)/|title=Kiss (Kita Sayang Sayang) by Lilis Karlina on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Chiki Chiki Bam Bam'' (in [[Telugu language]] [[India]] by Tippu in [[Aadi (2002 film)|Aadi]], 2002)\n* ''Beijo na Boca'' <small>/ Kiss in the Mouth /</small> (in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] by Mr. Jam)\n* ''D\u00e1-me Um Xoxo'' <small>/ Give me a Kiss /</small> (in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] by Tayti)\n* ''Selinho na Boca'' (in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] by [[Latino (singer)|Latino]] and [[Perlla]], 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Latino-Junto-E-Misturado/release/1988036|title=Latino (2) - Junto E Misturado|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''\u0418\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0448 \u043b\u0438 \u0431\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430\u043b\u043a\u0430?'' <small>/ Do you want a lollipop? /</small> (in [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] by [[Ruslan Maynov|Ruslan Mainov]], 1999<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whosampled.com/%D0%A0%D1%83%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%B0%D0%BD-%D0%9C%D1%8A%D0%B9%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2/%D0%91%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%BA%D0%B0/|title=\u0411\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430\u043b\u043a\u0430 by \u0420\u0443\u0441\u043b\u0430\u043d \u041c\u044a\u0439\u043d\u043e\u0432 on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''\u0414\u0430\u0439 \u043c\u0438 \u0446\u0435\u043b\u0443\u0432\u043a\u0430'' <small>/ Give me a kiss /</small> (in [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] by Tonita)\n* ''\u0425\u0438\u0449\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430'' <small>/ Predator /</small> (in [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] by Extra Nina)\n* ''Pusz-pussz'' (in [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] by [[Pa-D\u00f6-D\u0151]], 2003<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Pa-D%C3%B6-D%C5%91-Had-%C3%89nekelj%C3%BCnk-Mi-Is-Az-Id%C3%A9n/release/7431520|title=Pa-D\u00f6-D\u0151 - Had' \u00c9nekelj\u00fcnk Mi Is Az Id\u00e9n!|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>)\n* ''Kiss-Kiss'' <small>/ TCM-istele /</small> (in [[Romanian Language|Romanian]] by Vacan\u021ba Mare in Cu oltenii la eclips\u0103 show.)\n* ''Poljubi me'' <small>/ Kiss Me /</small> (in [[Slovenian language|Slovenian]] by Sandi Selim\u010di\u010d)\n* ''T\u00eb M\u00eb Jap\u00ebsh Nj\u00eb Puthje'' (in [[Albanian language|Albanian]] by Shk\u00eblqim Kola)\n\n==Samplings and adaptations==\n===Dj R'AN version===\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Kiss Kiss\n| cover      = Kiss-Kiss-DJ-RAN-Mohombi-Big-Ali.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = DJ R'AN featuring [[Mohombi]] and [[Big Ali]]\n| album      =\n| released   = September 26, 2016\n| format     = [[CD single]], downloads\n| recorded   = 2016\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]\n| length     = 2:51\n| label      = Madison Music\n| composer   =\n| lyricist   =\n| producer   = DJ R'AN\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|WMCDx2edfU8|\"Kiss Kiss\" by DJ R'AN feat. Mohombi and Big Ali}} }}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|fzvVl9ULUXk|\"Kiss Kiss\" by Ardian Bujupi and DJ R'AN feat. Mohombi and Big Ali}} }}\n}}\n* In 2016, French Dj R'AN (also known as Lucenzo Dj) released an adapted version of the song with new lyrics and added music. The single also titled \"Kiss Kiss\" and featured vocals by Swedish [[Mohombi]] and American [[Big Ali]] with additional work by [[Willy William]]. A music video was also released.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WMCDx2edfU8 YouTube Dj R'AN channel - Dj R'AN - KISS KISS feat Mohombi & Big Ali (official clip)]</ref> \n\nAn alternative release of the DJ R'AN version of \"Kiss Kiss\" was done in 2017 by Kosovar-German singer [[Ardian Bujupi]] with Dj R'AN featuring Mohombi and Big Ali.\n\n'''Other samplings'''\n* [[Yosi Piamenta]] released a version quoting ''Kol Hamesameach'', a [[Hebrew language]] passage from the [[Talmud]], but set to the melody of the song \"\u015e\u0131mar\u0131k\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whosampled.com/Piamenta/Kol-Hamesameach/|title=Kol Hamesameach by Piamenta on WhoSampled|website=WhoSampled|language=en|access-date=2018-09-23}}</ref>.\n* An Israeli 6PM news program on [[Channel 10 (Israel)|Channel 10]] named [[London et Kirschenbaum]] (named after the hosts, [[Yaron London]] and the program's late host [[Moti Kirschenbaum]]) is using a sample of this song in its opening theme.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://tarkantr.blogspot.com Single and Song Lyrics Information] in English